In this statement, President Obama acknowledges the retirement of Congressman John Kline and highlights his service in the Marine Corps and Congress. He mentions that Kline is married to an Army nurse and has a son who served in Iraq and Afghanistan. The President praises Kline's willingness to stand up for his beliefs and his commitment to working across party lines on education issues as Chairman of the House Education Committee. Obama expresses his desire to continue working with Kline in the future, particularly on efforts to provide equal opportunities for all children in America. He concludes by wishing Kline and his wife, Vicky, well in their future endeavors.